==Conference play==
The 2009<U+2013>10 season marked the third consecutive year that every Big Ten men<U+2019>s basketball conference regular-season and tournament game was nationally televised. In excess of 100 games appeared nationally on [[CBS]], [[ESPN]], [[ESPN2]] or the [[Big Ten Network]] every Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Saturday and Sunday during conference play beginning on December 29.  All ten games of the March 11 &ndash; 14, [[2010 Big Ten Conference Men's Basketball Tournament]] were nationally televised.<ref name=BTCA2MBTS>{{cite web|url=http://www.bigten.org/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/081909aad.html|title=Big Ten Conference Announces 2010 Men's Basketball Television Schedule: Every conference game and Big Ten Men's Basketball Tournament will be broadcast nationally on CBS Sports, ESPN, ESPN2 or the Big Ten Network|accessdate=2009-10-09|date=2009-08-19|publisher=CBS Interactive}}</ref>

With an eighteen-game in-conference schedule, each team met eight teams twice (home and away) and the two other teams only once.  The following were the one-time meetings for this season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bigten.org/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/072309aaa.html|title=2009-10 Men's Basketball Single Plays|accessdate=2009-10-18|date=2009-07-23|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]}}</ref>

