===Other tournaments===
{{mainarticle|2010 College Basketball Invitational|2010 CollegeInsider.com Tournament}}
The Big Ten did not have any entrants in the other post season tournaments.

===[[2010 NBA Draft]]===
Turner was the only Big Ten player selected in the 2010 Draft.<ref name=NBAD2010>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/draft2010/|title=Draft NY10|accessdate=2010-06-25|publisher=[[NBA.com]]}}</ref> The following All-Big Ten performers were listed as seniors: [[Tr<U+00E9>von Hughes]], [[Raymar Morgan]], [[Jason Bohannon]], [[DeShawn Sims]], [[Chris Kramer]], and [[Lawrence Westbrook]]. The following were All-Big Ten underclassmen, who declared early with the intent to hire agents:<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/nba/draft2010/news/story?id=5064218|title=Turner to enter NBA draft|date=April 7, 2010|accessdate=2010-04-08|author=Ford, Chad|publisher=[[ESPN.com]]}}</ref><ref name=MHeNd>{{cite web|url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/2010/basketball/ncaa/03/29/harris.nba.ap/index.html?eref=twitter_feed|title=Michigan's Harris entering NBA draft|accessdate=2010-03-29|date=2010-03-29|work=[[Sports Illustrated]]}}</ref> Neither withdrew his name from the draft-eligible list before the May 8 deadline.<ref name=21010NDeewl>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbssports.com/collegebasketball/story/13033792|title=2010 NBA Draft early entry watch list|accessdate=2010-05-09|publisher=[[CBS Sports]]}}</ref> [[Evan Turner]] and [[Manny Harris]]. The following were All-Big Ten underclassmen who entered their name in the draft but who did not hire agents and opted to return to college.<ref name=21010NDeewl/> [[Talor Battle]], [[Mike Davis (Illini)|Mike Davis]], [[JaJuan Johnson]], [[Demetri McCamey]], and [[E'Twaun Moore]].

